CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper July 7, 1956, pg. 3, reads: "Candidates - Alfred Reid (left) and Chester Williams were candidates for union offices in the election of Local 1397 of the United Steel Workers of America. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: United Steel Workers of American union officer candidates Albert Reid and Chester Williams standing on sidewalk with other men in background, next to building with sign reading "Re-elect 'Bill' Qualters..."
